Sri Lanka Reaches 207-4 at Lunch on Second Day of England Test in Cardiff

-- B y   C h r i s   E l s e r
-- 
2011-05-27T12:40:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/sri-lanka-reaches-207-4-at-lunch-on-second-day-of-england-test-in-cardiff.html
Sri Lanka  got 66 runs from Tharanga
Paranavitana to reach 207-4 at lunch on the second day of the
first Test with  England .  Paranavitana was bowled this morning by  Chris Tremlett ,
after combining for 93 runs with fellow opening batsman
 Tillakaratne Dilshan , who lost his wicket to Graeme Swann in
yesterday’s shortened day.  Thilan Samaraweera is on 38, and Prasanna Jayawardene on 21
going into the afternoon sessions. Yesterday’s action was
limited by rain, and Sri Lanka ended the day on 133-2.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  